4. FIREWALL AND NETWORK SECURITY DISCLAIMER
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------

THIS SOFTWARE IS DESIGNED TO MANAGE FIREWALL RULES AND NETWORK SECURITY
CONFIGURATIONS ACROSS MULTIPLE FIREWALL BACKENDS (INCLUDING BUT NOT LIMITED
TO iptables, nftables, firewalld, ufw, AND ipset). THE AUTHORS AND
CONTRIBUTORS:

  (a) DO NOT GUARANTEE that the Software will prevent all unauthorized
      access, network intrusions, denial of service attacks, data
      exfiltration, or any other security breach or compromise.

  (b) DO NOT GUARANTEE that firewall rules created, modified, imported, or
      managed by the Software will be complete, correct, properly ordered,
      free of conflicts, or effective for your specific security
      requirements, network topology, compliance obligations, or threat
      model.

  (c) ARE NOT RESPONSIBLE for any security incidents, data breaches, network
      outages, loss of connectivity, service disruptions, or system
      compromises that may occur while using, after using, or as a result
      of using the Software.

  (d) STRONGLY RECOMMEND that users independently verify all firewall rules,
      chain policies, zone configurations, and security settings before
      deploying them in production environments. The Software's rule
      summary and confirmation prompts do not substitute for independent
      expert review.

  (e) STRONGLY RECOMMEND that users create and maintain independent backups
      of all firewall configurations and network security policies using
      the built-in backup system or external tools before making changes.

  (f) STRONGLY RECOMMEND that users test all changes in non-production,
      isolated environments before applying them to production systems,
      and that users maintain out-of-band access to systems in case
      firewall misconfiguration causes loss of remote connectivity.

  (g) STRONGLY RECOMMEND that users do not rely on the Software as their
      sole means of network security, firewall management, or access
      control, and that defense-in-depth strategies incorporating multiple
      independent security controls are employed.

THE SOFTWARE MANAGES CRITICAL NETWORK INFRASTRUCTURE AT THE KERNEL LEVEL.
INCORRECT USE, MISCONFIGURATION, RULE CONFLICTS, OR SOFTWARE DEFECTS MAY
RESULT IN: COMPLETE LOSS OF NETWORK CONNECTIVITY; EXPOSURE OF SERVICES TO
UNAUTHORIZED ACCESS; DENIAL OF SERVICE TO LEGITIMATE TRAFFIC; LOSS, CORRUPTION,
OR INTERCEPTION OF DATA IN TRANSIT; OR FULL SYSTEM COMPROMISE. USERS ASSUME
ALL RISK ASSOCIATED WITH THE USE OF THIS SOFTWARE FOR MANAGING NETWORK
SECURITY.

